      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <updateDate>2015-10-29T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2015-10-29</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Black Hills National Cemetery Boundary Expansion Act </strong></p> <p>This bill transfers jurisdiction over certain public land from the Department of the Interior to the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) for inclusion in the Black Hills National Cemetery. </p> <p>Upon a determination by the VA that all or a portion of such transferred land shall not be used for cemetery purposes, the VA shall: (1) notify Interior and transfer jurisdiction of the land back to Interior, and (2) be responsible for any decontamination costs necessary for restoration of the lands to the public lands. </p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-11-04T21:55:26Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        </item>
        <item>
          <versionCode>01</versionCode>
          <name>Reported to Senate amended</name>
          <updateDate>2016-09-06T15:32:44Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2016-09-06</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Black Hills National Cemetery Boundary Expansion Act </strong></p> <p>(Sec. 3) This bill transfers jurisdiction over approximately 200 acres of Bureau of Land Management land from the Department of the Interior to the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) for inclusion in the Black Hills National Cemetery, South Dakota.</p> <p>The VA shall reimburse Interior for reasonable transfer costs, including survey costs.</p> <p> The cemetery's boundary is modified to include such federal land. </p> <p>For the period such land is under the administrative jurisdiction of the VA, it shall be withdrawn from all forms of appropriation under the public land laws, including the mining laws, the mineral leasing laws, and the geothermal leasing laws.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-11-21T23:02:42Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Reported to Senate amended</actionDesc>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
